@startuml
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
title 08 – Dziedziczenie wielokrotne i algorytm MRO (C3)

class Flyable {
  + fly() : str
  + altitude() : float
}

class Swimmable {
  + swim() : str
  + depth() : float
}

class Walkable {
  + walk() : str
  + speed() : float
}

class LoggerMixin {
  - _log: list[str]
  --
  + log(msg: str) : None
  + get_log() : list[str]
}

class TimestampMixin {
  - _created_at: datetime
  --
  + created_at : datetime  <<property>>
  + age_seconds() : float
}

class Duck {
  - _name: str
  --
  + __init__(name: str)
  + __str__() : str
  + describe() : str
}

class AmphibiousVehicle {
  - _fuel: float
  --
  + __init__(fuel: float)
  + describe() : str
}

class LoggedEvent {
  - _name: str
  --
  + __init__(name: str)
  + __str__() : str
}

Flyable    <|-- Duck
Swimmable  <|-- Duck
Walkable   <|-- Duck
Swimmable  <|-- AmphibiousVehicle
Walkable   <|-- AmphibiousVehicle
LoggerMixin    <|-- LoggedEvent
TimestampMixin <|-- LoggedEvent

note bottom of Duck
  MRO Pythona (algorytm C3):
  Duck → Flyable → Swimmable → Walkable → object
  Python przeszukuje klasy od lewej do prawej,
  unikając duplikatów.
  ""Duck.__mro__""
end note

note right of LoggedEvent
  Mixiny to klasy bez własnego stanu
  dziedzinowego – dodają tylko zachowania.
  Konwencja: sufiks ""Mixin"".
end note
@enduml
